Author-Name: Sandra Renfro Callaghan 
Author-Name: P. Jane Saly 
Author-Name: Chandra Subramaniam 
Title: The Timing of Option Repricing 
Abstract:
 We investigate whether executive stock option repricings are
 systematically timed to coincide with favorable movements in the company's
 stock price. For a sample of 236 repricing events, we observe sharp
 increases in stock price in the 20-day period following the repricing
 date. In addition, repricing dates tend to either precede the release of
 good news or follow the release of bad news in the quarterly earnings
 announcements. Since information about stock option repricing is not
 generally released to the public around the repricing date, these findings
 suggest that CEOs opportunistically manage the timing of the option
 repricing date. Copyright 2004 by The American Finance Association. 
